Terms and Conditions for Private Home Automation SMS Bot

This SMS service is a private, family-only home automation bot used to send commands to a personal Control4 home system.

Eligibility:
This service is only for authorized family members who have been manually added to the allowlist by the system owner. Unauthorized use is not permitted.

Message purpose:
Users may text commands to control approved home automation functions and may receive confirmation, help, error, or security-related replies. No marketing
or promotional messages are sent.

Message frequency:
Message frequency varies based on user interaction. The bot generally replies only when an authorized user sends a command or request.

Message and data rates:
Message and data rates may apply according to the user’s mobile carrier plan.

Opt out:
Users can stop using the service at any time by texting STOP or by asking the system owner to remove their phone number from the allowlist.

Help:
Users can text HELP to receive available bot commands.

Privacy:
Personal information is handled according to the Privacy Policy for this service.

Safety:
Users are responsible for sending only appropriate commands. Commands may affect physical devices such as lights, doors, locks, garage doors, or other
smart home equipment.

Contact:
For questions, help, or removal requests, contact the owner of this private home automation system.
